{"lemma":"لَقْطَةٌ","slug":"لَقْطَةٌ","root":"ل.ق.ط","root_slug":"ل-ق-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-ق-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37913","n37918","n37919"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37913","headword_ar":"لَقَطَهُ","root":"lqT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, * Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqoTN","text_ar":"لَقْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He picked it up, took it up, raised it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without trouble"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AltqThu","text_ar":"التقطهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took it from a place where it was not thought to be;"},{"kind":"text","text":"this being the primary signification: and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) It is said of a man: and you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqaTa AlT~aAy^iru AlHab~a","text_ar":"لَقَطَ الطَّايِرُ الحَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bird picked up from the ground the grains"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) The Arabs say to a calumniator, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Einodaka diykFA yalotaqiTu","text_ar":"اـِنَّ عِنْدَكَ دِيكًا يَلْتَقِطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaSaY","text_ar":"الحَصَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily thou hast a cock that picks up pebbles"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And it is said in a proverb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSayoda Alqunofu*i A^amo laqoTahu","text_ar":"اَصَيْدَ القُنْفُذِ اَمْ لَقْطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is it by the hunting of the hedgehog"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the picking up thereof from the ground?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] applied to a poor man who becomes rich suddenly. (TA.) [In Freytag's Arab. Prov. (i. 726,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSayodu Alqunofu*i A^amo luqaTapN","text_ar":"اَصَيْدُ القُنْفُذِ اَمْ لُقَطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and there asserted to be said of him who finds a thing which he had not sought: or, accord. to Sharafed-Deen, of a thing of the nature of which we may be uncertain.] You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqaTotu AlEilomi","text_ar":"لَقَطْتُ العِلْمِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Alkutubi","text_ar":"مِنَ الكُتُبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I picked up science,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge, from books;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I acquired science,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge, from this and that book."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqaTotu","text_ar":"لَقَطْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbiEahu","text_ar":"اَصَابِعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I took off his fingers, by cutting, without"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the main part of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","Mgh","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n37918","headword_ar":"لُقْطَةٌ","root":"lqT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqaTN","text_ar":"لَقَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", throughout the first sentence. ―         -b2-  Accord. to Lth, it [also] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who repeatedly and perseveringly seeks after things to be picked up, and picks them up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and some say, that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luqaTapN","text_ar":"لُقَطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who picks up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the more common and correct signification of this latter is “ property which is found, ” as before stated. (IAth.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n37919","headword_ar":"لُقَطَةٌ","root":"lqT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqaTN","text_ar":"لَقَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", throughout the first sentence: — and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luqoTapN","text_ar":"لُقْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}